Notes on running jtreg for panc.

Install Jtreg:
===============================================================================
Debian derivitives
    sudo apt-get install jtreg


Run Jtreg for panc:
===============================================================================
$> cd tests
$> jtreg -jdk:/path/to/installed/jdk7 -Xbootclasspath/p:path/to/dist/lib/panc.jar tools/panc/

    -jdk: The Java Virtual Machine in this path will be used to run the tests.
    -Xbootclasspath/p:  prepends the panc.jar on the boot classpath. Ensures the panc versions of the compiler are used.



